1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:26,641
Prayer to Saint Herman of Alaska Pray slowly. Read with attention.

2
00:00:26,641 --> 00:00:35,833
O Holy Father Herman, you left the peaceful lakes of Valaam to bring the light of the Gospel to the remote shores of Alaska. Embracing poverty and the harsh wilderness,

3
00:00:35,833 --> 00:00:45,025
you became a father to the native people, defending them against greed and injustice, and teaching them the beauty of Christ's love.

4
00:00:45,025 --> 00:00:55,722
O quiet elder, on Spruce Island you lived in a simple wooden cell, surrounded by the wild forest and the sea. You sought no earthly glory, finding your joy in constant

5
00:00:55,722 --> 00:01:06,419
prayer and the company of the angels. Teach us to love silence, to find peace in times of isolation, and to see the beauty of God's creation.

6
00:01:06,419 --> 00:01:16,542
We remember your boundless charity, O holy protector. When deadly diseases struck, you stayed by the sick, nursing them with your own hands. You gathered the orphans,

7
00:01:16,542 --> 00:01:26,665
teaching them to praise God and caring for them as your own children. Look upon us today and protect our families and children from all harm.

8
00:01:26,665 --> 00:01:35,915
We remember your inspiring words: 'From this day forth, from this hour, from this minute, let us love God above all, and do His holy will.' Help us, Father Herman, to

9
00:01:35,915 --> 00:01:45,165
put these words into action, turning away from our old habits and dedicating our lives to the love of our Creator.

10
00:01:45,165 --> 00:01:55,736
Saint Herman of Alaska, pray to God for us. Amen.

